Entry.translation:
This is a template geodata model to be used for modeling according CHBase, the "base modules of the Swiss Confederation for minimal geodata models".
Prepare your model according CHBase by importing the needed CHBase packages (i.e. modules) to your model.
Start modeling! Make sure to apply CHBase definitions wherever appropriate!
Questions? drop a line at "models@geo.admin.ch"

Base modules of the Swiss Confederation for minimal geodata models
Contains: - geometry (LV03, LV95) - localisation - catalogues - administrative units - object updating - graphic annotations
Available online: http://models.geo.admin.ch/CHBase
INTERLIS 2.3 geodata model file of the model template MyModelTemplate_V2
FORMAT BASED ON Angle_DMS_S (Degrees ":" Minutes ":" Seconds)
FORMAT BASED ON GregorianDate (Year "-" Month "-" Day)
REFSYSTEM BASKET BaseTimeSystems~INTERLIS.TIMESYSTEMS OBJECTS OF CALENDAR: GregorianCalendar OBJECTS OF TIMEOFDAYSYS: UTC;
REFSYSTEM BASKET BCoordSys~CoordSys.CoordsysTopic OBJECTS OF GeoCartesian2D: CHLV95 OBJECTS OF GeoHeight: SwissOrthometricAlt;
FUNCTION myClass( Object : OBJECT OF ANYSTRUCTURE) : STRUCTURE;
FUNCTION isSubClass( potSubClass : STRUCTURE; potSuperClass : STRUCTURE) : BOOLEAN;

FUNCTION areAreas( Objects : OBJECTS OF ANYCLASS; SurfaceBag : ATTRIBUTE OF @ Objects RESTRICTION ( BAG {0..*} OF ANYSTRUCTURE ); SurfaceAttr : ATTRIBUTE OF @ Objects RESTRICTION ( SURFACE )) : BOOLEAN;

FUNCTION inEnumRange( Enum : ENUMVAL; MinVal : ENUMTREEVAL; MaxVal : ENUMTREEVAL) : BOOLEAN;
FUNCTION elementCount( bag : BAG {0..*} OF ANYSTRUCTURE) : NUMERIC;
